ongering continues in Washington, following my reporting last week that the=
 Harris campaign hobbled across the threshold with millions of dollars in d=
ebt. The Democratic National Committee, in particular, is in a dire state, =
and will need to fundraise in the midst of extreme donor fatigue. Of course=
, layoffs and party leadership transitions are de rigueur following an unsu=
ccessful cycle, but the profundity of the loss, with almost every county sw=
inging toward Trump, has instigated more than the typical Democratic soul-s=
earching.

